Text.Value: How can you talk about cheese at a time like this?
I mean... surely our wine couldn't have been poisoned?
I only jest, Flaerith!
...Oh. I see.
In the Sword Coast? In your dreams, more like!
Best not tell them I prefer a pink.
Oh yeah, the cheese and ale festival a few years back. Some very funky cheese.
Now, Flaerith - I'm just saying white wine is better.
Has this happened to you before?
Maybe for plebs.
You know if cheese affects you that badly, there are spells for it?
This red is the best wine in the entire Sword Coast.
At least white wine doesn't stain tongues and teeth.
Oooh, I bet this'll be fun.
Fight, fight, FIGHT!
You wound me, Ontur. Truly.
You know, I really do think red is the best wine.
So am I. That cheese was pure poison.
Boring!
...Excuse me, how dare you?!
Quite right, it's - wait, what do you mean 'again'?
Oh, this is really awful. Truly terrible.
Swallow a cork and die.
I'm talking about the murder attempt.
No, they stain their drinker's reputation instead.
Yes... terrible. I can't believe this is happening again.
What, on a hot summer's day? Madness.
This should be good.
I wouldn't debase myself so much.
Depends - did you drink the pink?
The only thing that's too harsh are these tannins.
Did I drink the pink? Shit...
I think... I think I was too harsh, Ontur. My apologies.

Synopsis: When the Wine Festival begins, some ADs will be playing in row. This is one of them.
